author: Jarrett Prendergast
title: Mariners Make Latest Offseason Move Official
text:
The Seattle Mariners are looking to get back to the postseason next year.
In 2022, they were a postseason team and even won a series.
But, they fell short of the playoffs in 2023.
The AL West is one of the toughest divisions in baseball.
The Mariners have to compete with both the Texas Rangers and Houston Astros for a playoff berth.
For Seattle, they knew they needed to make additions to their roster.
One player they went out and signed away from their rival is catcher Mitch Garver.
According to the Mariners, they signed Garver to a two-year contract.
Adding some Garv-sauce to the squad üëä
We have signed C/DH Mitch Garver to a 2-year contract through 2025 with a mutual option that runs through the 2026 season.
üîó

[December 28, 2023]
Garver is coming off one of the best offensive seasons of his career.
He batted .270 with 19 home runs, 50 RBI, and an OPS of .870.
Garver now joins a loaded catcher‚Äôs room in Seattle.
Cal Raleigh and Garver will be a great one-two punch for the Mariners.
It is rare to get quality offensive production from a catcher.
Well, the Mariners should be able to get that from both of theirs.
Seattle has plenty of work to do to compete in the AL West next year.
One spot they can use some help is in the outfield.
They traded away Jarred Kelenic and Teoscar Hernandez is a free agent.
Outside of Julio Rodriguez, the Mariners do not have any proven outfielders.
It will be interesting to see what other moves the Mariners make.
If they are serious about contending their front office should be aggressive in free agency.

title: Two people die after car collides with ambulance transporting elderly man - The Courier
text:
Two people die after car collides with ambulance transporting elderly man By Press Association December 28 2023, 9.26pm Share Two people die after car collides with ambulance transporting elderly man Share via Facebook Twitter Linkedin Whatsapp Messenger Email Post link https://www.thecourier.co.uk/news/uk-world/4852830/two-people-die-after-car-collides-with-ambulance-transporting-elderly-man/ Copy Link Two people are dead after a collision between a car and an ambulance transporting an elderly man in Suffolk (File image/PA)
Two people are dead after a collision between a car and an ambulance transporting an elderly man in Suffolk.
Emergency services were called to the B1506 Bury Road, between Newmarket and Kentford, at about 7.30pm on December 19.
One of those killed was a woman in her 70s, who was driving the car, a blue Volkswagen Golf.
The other was a man in his 90s, a passenger in the ambulance, who died after being taken to Addenbrooke‚Äôs Hospital, Suffolk Police said.
The female ambulance driver suffered serious injuries and was also taken to hospital.
Police are appealing for witnesses, who can call 101, quoting SC-19122023-302.

title: Boeing va a la huelga por primera vez en 16 a√±os
text: Secciones Servicios Destacamos EP Viernes, 13 de septiembre 2024, 11:46 Necesitas ser registrado para acceder a esta funcionalidad. Opciones para compartir El sindicato de los trabajadores de Boeing en en la regi√≥n de Seattle (EE.UU.) ha convocado una huelga por primera vez en 16 a√±os y ha rechazado la oferta del fabricante para subir un 25% los salarios. Seg√∫n recoge DPA, el 94,65% de los trabajadores votaron que no a la oferta que lanz√≥ Boeing para evitar los paros, que contemplaba una subida salarial del 25% en cuatro a√±os, mejorar en las coberturas sanitarias y las jubilaciones, dado que el sindicato IAM hab√≠a pedido inicialmente un incremento del 40% en los salarios. Adem√°s, el 96% apoy√≥ la convocatoria de huelga. La huelga ha comenzado a las 00.00 hora local de este viernes para unos 30.000 trabajadores. Los representantes sindicales han se√±alado en una rueda de prensa recogida por 'Bloomberg' que los puntos del acuerdo no eran lo suficientemente buenos y que la oferta no compensaba los 16 a√±os de estancamiento salarial, el aumento de los gastos sanitarios y la deslocalizaci√≥n de miles de empleos sindicales. Por su parte, Boeing ha emitido un comunicado en el que muestra su compromiso para restablecer la relaci√≥n con los trabajadores y el sindicato, adem√°s de volver a la mesa para alcanzar un nuevo acuerdo. Boeing atraviesa una crisis de reputaci√≥n, de seguridad y econ√≥mica desde 2019, cuando dos aviones 737 MAX sufrieron accidentes fatales. Tras esto, se han producido otros incidentes, como la ca√≠da de una parte del fuselaje de un avi√≥n de Alaska Airlines a principios de este a√±o.
